        <h1 class="title" id="page-title">GNU Hackers Meeting</h1>                                <div id="content-output"> 
          <div id="node-42" class="node post clear-block">



  <div class="meta post-info">
  
    </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h2>Calling all GNU Hackers!</h2>
<hr />
<em> The <a href="http://www.gnu.org/ghm/2009/">GNU Hackers Meeting 2009</a> is the third annual meeting for GNU maintainers and active contributors.<br />
</em>
<p>The theme of this meeting is the continued advancement of the GNU system. We want to encourage discussion and talks on the following topics:</p>
<ul>
<li> New challenges for software freedom and the GNU system</li>
<li>Technical goals for the future</li>
<li>Organisational development</li>
</ul>
<p>Recent shifts in the computing landscape, such as web services and<br />
mobile computing, present new challenges to software freedom. </p>
<p><i>How can we extend our freedom into these areas?</i></p>
<p><i>What new technical ideas do we need to understand?  </i></p>
<p><i>What new software do we need to provide to keep our freedom? </i></p>
<p><i>What is the best way to organise our work, inspire others and promote the ethical philosophy of software freedom today?</i></p>
<p><center><br />
<img src="http://www.gnu.org/ghm/2009/logo.png" /><br />
</center></p>
  </div>

